Volkswagen’s Audi Unit August Sales Rise 17% to 94,100 Units

-- B y   R a j i v   S e k h r i
-- 
2011-09-08T09:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/volkswagen-s-audi-unit-august-sales-rise-17-to-94-100-units.html
Volkswagen AG (VOW)  unit Audi’s August
sales rose 17.1 percent worldwide to 94,100 units compared with
the year-ago period, the company said in an e-mailed statement
today.  German sales grew 20.2 percent thanks to a growing list of
corporate customers. Sales in China, including Hong Kong, rose
25.5 percent. In Brazil, sales increased 67 percent.  “The signs are also favorable for the A6 Avant, introduced
by the company into its first markets in late August,” said
 Peter Schwarzenbauer , Audi board member for marketing and sales.
“Orders for it are much higher than we expected.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
